-- Step 1: Filter objects classified as SN II with probability > 0.6, ranking=1, classifier='lc_classifier'
WITH snii_objects AS
  (SELECT o.oid
   FROM OBJECT o
   INNER JOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
   WHERE p.class_name = 'SNII'
     AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
     AND p.probability > 0.6
     AND p.ranking = 1
     AND o.firstmjd <= 59910 -- 2022-12-31 MJD

     AND o.lastmjd >= 58549 -- 2019-01-01 MJD
), -- Step 2: Filter objects with more than 50 detections in 2019-2022
objects_with_ndet AS
  (SELECT o.oid
   FROM OBJECT o
   WHERE o.oid IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM snii_objects)
     AND o.ndet > 50 ), -- Step 3: Filter detections within date range and bands g (fid=1) and r (fid=2)
detections_filtered AS
  (SELECT d.oid,
          d.candid,
          d.magpsf,
          d.sigmapsf,
          d.mjd,
          d.fid
   FROM detection d
   WHERE d.oid IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM objects_with_ndet)
     AND d.mjd BETWEEN 58549 AND 59910
     AND d.fid IN (1,
                   2) ), -- Step 4: Filter objects with initial rise rate > 0.5 mag/day in g and r bands
magstat_filtered AS
  (SELECT m.oid,
          m.fid,
          m.dmdt_first
   FROM magstat m
   WHERE m.oid IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM objects_with_ndet)
     AND m.fid IN (1,
                   2)
     AND m.dmdt_first > 0.5 ) -- Final: Retrieve detections with associated initial rise rate

SELECT d.oid,
       d.candid,
       d.magpsf,
       d.sigmapsf,
       m.dmdt_first,
       CASE d.fid
           WHEN 1 THEN 'g'
           WHEN 2 THEN 'r'
       END AS band,
       d.mjd
FROM detections_filtered d
INNER JOIN magstat_filtered m ON d.oid = m.oid
AND d.fid = m.fid
ORDER BY d.mjd;
